&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define the Vision:&lt;/strong&gt; Execute a long-term growth strategy for Jewelry. You’ll identify the next big shifts in vintage, estate, and contemporary segments and move first to capture them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Curate the Marketplace:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with Dealer Relations and Art Research to onboard the world’s leading estates and brands. You’ll ensure our selection has the &lt;strong&gt;unmatched breadth and quality&lt;/strong&gt; our buyers expect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empower Our Partners:&lt;/strong&gt; Build trusted relationships with top dealers, providing them with the data-driven insights and pricing strategies they need to thrive on our platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analyze &amp;amp; Optimize:&lt;/strong&gt; Dive deep into marketplace KPIs—conversion, traffic, and inventory health—to turn raw data into actionable growth levers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Cross-Functionally:&lt;/strong&gt; You’ll succeed alongside the Product, Marketing, and Customer Experience teams to advocate for the features and tools that elevate the jewelry-buying journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; 8+ years in category/inventory management within luxury e-commerce, auction houses, or the jewelry industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analytical Rigor:&lt;/strong&gt; You are comfortable with marketplace KPIs and use data to tell a story and drive decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Knowledge:&lt;/strong&gt; A deep, &quot;insider&quot; understanding of fine, vintage, and designer jewelry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Influence:&lt;/strong&gt; The ability to move complex initiatives forward by influencing cross-functional teams and external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional presentation skills, you can speak &quot;luxury&quot; to a dealer and &quot;data&quot; to an executive.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
